<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Married At First Sight's Stacey Hampton is in the process of removing a tattoo dedicated to her ex-fiance, Rebels Adelaide president Shane Michael Smith.</p>

<p>The 26-year-old reality TV star is covered in many inkings from her time with the bikie boss, including a large stomach tattoo dedicated to her late brother, which she often keeps well-hidden.</p>

<p>But on Tuesday, Stacey revealed on Instagram that she was getting a tattoo of Shane's name gradually lasered off her hand.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video </p>

<p>Saying goodbye: Married At First Sight's Stacey Hampton is getting a tattoo dedicated to her Rebels' bikie boss ex lasered off her hand</p>

<p>During an Instagram Q&amp;A, Stacey showed off Shane's name in cursive on her hand. The tattoo appears to be slowly fading due to her regular laser appointments.</p>

<p>The blonde bombshell dated Shane, 37, for several years until their split in July 2017, a month before he was convicted of bashing two nightclub bouncers. </p>

<p>The former couple share custody of two sons, Kruz, two, and Kosta, four.</p>

